{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba6fb1d3-a035-45e5-bf3f-4404b00ebfcc","content":"\n\nHere's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead (use version matching your xunit version, e.g. 2.9.3):\n\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (in a `<PropertyGroup>`):\n\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n4. **Optionally**, enable the newer `dotnet test` integration:\n\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   ```\n\n5. Run your tests with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly as an executable (MTP makes your test project an entry point).\n\nThat's the core swap — `xunit.runner.visualstudio` → `xunit.runner.mtp` + the MSBuild property. Everything else (test authoring, `[Fact]`, `[Theory]`, etc.) stays the same.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79463c8b-f3fa-4580-a6d0-e0f999de1ef5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":365},"id":"0b1c5241-10a9-482b-8fcf-c01f30ca19de","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:41:16.649Z","parentId":"b5ef1318-9f13-46b1-ae14-1e326ad04fec"}
